better accuracy than the Friedewald equation in the

tr.td: Person consulting for explanation of examination or test findings (ICD-10 - Z71.2)

td.paragraph: Routine
blood work was obtained today as well as ESR, CRP, ferritin, and ANA panel
for further evaluation of his fatigue. The blood work was performed without complication,
and the results will be reviewed and discussed at his next visit. All questions and concerns were answered and
addressed. A heart-healthy diet and a healthy lifestyle were encouraged and
endorsed. He is to follow up in one week for lab work results, or sooner should
symptoms worsen, progress, or if new symptoms arise. He agrees to the plan of
care.

Time Spent: Total time spent 84 minutes in face-to-face conversation, examination, reviewing records, discussing treatment options and procedures, pathophysiology, and anatomy. Diet and lifestyle modifications were discussed in great detail. Images were personally reviewed by me in front of the patient and/or family member and explained on our graphic diagram. Treatment options, risks, benefits and alternative treatments discussed with the patient in detail. All questions and concerns answered.

tr.td: Scribed by Devendra Bisht and Phoebe Tarta under the supervision of Dr. Rishi Bajaj

td.paragraph: Labs
reviewed and discussed today that revealed
vitamin D deficiency at 27 and hemoglobin level at 17.9. CBC, CMP,
lipid panel, TSH, ferritin, and CRP 18.1. A1C was 5.4. He was advised
to increase hydration to support hematologic balance and to initiate
OTC vitamin D supplementation with at least 2000 IU daily. He will
follow up in the office within 1-2 weeks for reassessment.
Heart-healthy lifestyle counseling was provided. The patient agrees
with the plan.

Patient was informed of the telemedicine visit by our office staff. Telemedicine was described in detail to the patient as the use of synchronous video and audio communication to provide clinical care from a distance. A telemedicine visit can provide the same medical standard of care for specific conditions. The patient was informed that the practice staff located at the provider's office would assist in carrying out any recommendations and clinical care.
Patient Location: Home
Lack of strict HIPPA Rules. Patient expressed verbal interest in the telemedicine visit and granted consent to proceed.
